From: nvukobratTT <nvukobratTT@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 23:50:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/9] =?UTF-8?q?fix(StableHLO=E2=86=92TTIR):=20fix=20PadOp?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20interior-padding=20index=20order=20(row-major)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

StableHLOToTTIROpPadOpConversionPattern converts stablehlo.pad with
interior padding by computing flat 1D scatter indices, then calling
flattenTensor on the source, and scattering source elements into a FullOp
tensor.

Bug: the index enumeration loop started from current_index=0 (outermost
dimension), producing indices in column-major order. flattenTensor uses
row-major order (last dimension fastest). The mismatch placed source
elements at wrong positions — 95%+ of elements misplaced in a 2D RoPE
repro (max error 14.6×).

Fix: replace the hand-rolled carry loop with a recursive row-major
enumeration (innermost dimension varies fastest), matching the flattening
order.

Impact: fixes all models using out[..., 0::2] = val strided assignment
(RoPE), including Wan2.1-T2V, Flux, LLaMA, Mistral, SD3.

Fixes: https://github.com/nvukobratTT/tt-xla/issues/5
---
 .../StableHLOToTTIRPatterns.cpp               | 43 ++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 25 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/Conversion/StableHLOToTTIR/StableHLOToTTIRPatterns.cpp b/lib/Conversion/StableHLOToTTIR/StableHLOToTTIRPatterns.cpp
index e97cfc36b..847a53ca0 100644
--- a/lib/Conversion/StableHLOToTTIR/StableHLOToTTIRPatterns.cpp
+++ b/lib/Conversion/StableHLOToTTIR/StableHLOToTTIRPatterns.cpp
@@ -5600,33 +5600,26 @@ public:
         lowerbounds.push_back(counter);
       }
       llvm::SmallVector<int64_t> flatIndices;
-      flatIndices.append(counters.begin(), counters.end());
-      int64_t numIndices = 1;
-
-      size_t current_index = 0;
-      while (current_index < counters.size() &&
-             counters[counters.size() - 1] <
-                 upperbounds[upperbounds.size() - 1]) {
-        counters[current_index] += steps[current_index];
-        bool reset = false;
-        while (current_index < counters.size() &&
-               counters[current_index] >= upperbounds[current_index]) {
-          counters[current_index] = lowerbounds[current_index];
-          current_index++;
-          if (current_index < counters.size()) {
-            counters[current_index] += steps[current_index];
-          }
-          reset = true;
-        }
-        if (current_index >= counters.size()) {
-          break;
+      int64_t numIndices = 0;
+
+      // Enumerate indices in row-major order (innermost dimension varies
+      // fastest) so the order matches how flattenTensor linearizes the source
+      // tensor. The previous outermost-first iteration produced column-major
+      // index order, which mismatched the row-major-flattened update tensor and
+      // placed source elements at wrong output positions.
+      // See: https://github.com/nvukobratTT/tt-xla/issues/5
+      std::function<void(int64_t)> enumerate = [&](int64_t dim) {
+        if (static_cast<size_t>(dim) == counters.size()) {
+          flatIndices.append(counters.begin(), counters.end());
+          numIndices++;
+          return;
         }
-        if (reset) {
-          current_index = 0;
+        for (counters[dim] = lowerbounds[dim];
+             counters[dim] < upperbounds[dim]; counters[dim] += steps[dim]) {
+          enumerate(dim + 1);
         }
-        flatIndices.append(counters.begin(), counters.end());
-        numIndices++;
-      }
+      };
+      enumerate(0);
       auto inputType =
           mlir::cast<RankedTensorType>(adaptor.getOperand().getType());
 
